   "info" : "<table width=\"100%\" summary=\"page for StrikeDur\"><tr><td>StrikeDur</td><td style=\"text-align: right;\">R Documentation</td></tr></table>\\n<h2>Strikes Duration </h2>\\n<h3>Description</h3>\\n<p>a cross-section from 1968 to 1976\\n</p>\\n<p><em>number of observations</em> :  566\\n</p>\\n<p><em>country</em> :  United States\\n</p>\\n<h3>Usage</h3>\\n<pre>data(StrikeDur)</pre>\\n<h3>Format</h3>\\n<p>A dataframe containing :\\n</p>\\n<dl>\\n<dt>dur</dt><dd><p>duration of the strike in days</p>\\n</dd>\\n<dt>gdp</dt><dd><p>measure of stage of business cycle (deviation of monthly log industrial production in manufacturing from prediction from OLS on time, time-squared and monthly dummies)</p>\\n</dd>\\n</dl>\\n<h3>Source</h3>\\n<p>Kennan, J. (1985) &ldquo;The Duration of Contract strikes in U.S. Manufacturing&rdquo;, <em>Journal of Econometrics</em>, <b>28</b>, 5-28.\\n</p>\\n<h3>References</h3>\\n<p>Cameron, A.C.  and  P.K.  Trivedi (2005) <em>Microeconometrics : methods and applications</em>, Cambridge, pp. 574&ndash;5 abd 582.\\n</p>\\n<h3>See Also</h3>\\n<p><code>Index.Source</code>, <code>Index.Economics</code>, <code>Index.Econometrics</code>, <code>Index.Observations</code></p>\\n",
